  "prompt": "Which are the best YouTube channels for UPSC preparation besides all materials?",
  "response": "Certainly! Here are some highly recommended YouTube channels for UPSC (Union Public Service Commission) preparation:\n\n1. **Unacademy:** This channel provides lectures from top educators and covers various subjects required for the UPSC exams. It includes live classes, recorded lectures, and exam strategies.\n\n2. **Mrunal Patel:** Known for his detailed explanations on economics, Mrunal Patel's channel is invaluable for understanding this complicated subject. He also covers other topics and provides analyses of current affairs.\n\n3. **Study IQ Education:** This channel covers current affairs, general knowledge, and various subjects needed for UPSC exams. They have concise and informative videos that can help in last-minute preparation.\n\n4. **Vision IAS:** Vision IAS is a coaching institute that also offers online lectures on their YouTube channel, covering a wide range of subjects and current affairs discussions important for the UPSC exams.\n\n5. **Rau\u2019s IAS Study Circle:** This channel offers lectures and insights from one of the renowned coaching institutes for IAS exams. It provides detailed subject-wise lectures, mock tests, and interview preparation tips.\n\n6. **BYJU\u2019S IAS:** BYJU\u2019S focuses on providing comprehensive subject videos, strategy sessions, and current affairs updates that are crucial for UPSC exam preparation.\n\n7. **Drishti IAS:** This channel offers lectures in both English and Hindi, covering detailed topics, daily current affairs, and motivational sessions related to UPSC preparation.\n\n8. **IASbaba:** Known for its integrated approach, IASbaba provides daily current affairs updates, static subject knowledge videos, and interactive sessions especially tailored for UPSC aspirants.\n\nEach of these channels has a unique style and approach, so it's beneficial to explore them and see which one aligns best with your learning preferences.",
